==Latin==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[res loquitur ipsa|rēs loquitur ipsa]] ([http://books.google.is/books?id=bXGJuX1mDrwC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA201])
===Etymology===
From {{term|res|rēs|thing|lang=la}} + {{term|ipsa||herself|lang=la}}, the feminine of {{term|ipse||himself|lang=la}} because {{term|res|rēs|lang=la}} is a feminine word + {{term|loquitur||she speaks|lang=la}} the third-person form of {{term|loquor||I speak|lang=la}}. Literally meaning "the thing itself speaks" or "the matter itself speaks".
===Phrase===
'''[[res#Latin|rēs]] [[ipsa]] [[loquor#Latin|loquitur]]'''
# the thing [[speak]]s for [[itself]]

